where do united airlines flights land from minneapolis in chicago ord

United Airlines flights from Minneapolis typically arrive at Terminal 1 or Terminal 2 at Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD). While Terminal 5 is also used by United Airlines, it's primarily for international arrivals and some domestic flights. It's worth noting that terminal assignments can change, so it's always a good idea to verify the terminal for your specific flight close to your departure date, either through the United Airlines website, the official airport website, or by checking the flight information displays upon arrival at the airport【11†source】.
can i walk from terminal 1 to 3 in ord?

Yes, you can walk between Terminals 1, 2, and 3 at Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD). The terminals are connected by pedestrian walkways, allowing passengers to move easily without having to exit security. The walk between Terminals 1 and 3 can be made through a series of corridors and moving walkways, and it's well marked with signs directing passengers. The time it takes to walk between terminals can vary based on walking speed and specific gate locations but plan for it to take several minutes. If you're transferring flights and have limited time, be sure to check the gate information for your connecting flight to plan accordingly.
which lounges do i have access to at ord with my saffire chase card?

At Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD), with your Chase Sapphire card, you typically have access to lounges through the Priority Pass network. However, according to the Chase website, there is only one lounge available to Priority Pass members at ORD, located in the International Terminal 5. This is the Swissport Lounge. To access it, you must have a boarding pass for an outgoing international flight and be a Priority Pass member. The lounge offers a variety of amenities including Wi-Fi, refreshments, a hot and cold buffet in the evening, and more. It's open daily from 7 a.m. to 9 p.m【19†source】. 

Please note that access policies may change, and it's always a good idea to check the specific benefits of your Chase Sapphire card and the Priority Pass website for the most up-to-date information before your travels.

can i walk to it without having an international ticket from terminal 3 post security?

No, you generally cannot walk to Terminal 5 from Terminal 3 at ORD without exiting security, especially without an international boarding pass. Terminal 5 is primarily used for international flights and is separate from Terminals 1, 2, and 3, which are connected post-security. To access Terminal 5, you would need to exit security and take the Airport Transit System (ATS) or a shuttle bus, and then re-enter security at Terminal 5, which typically requires an international boarding pass.
